docs\api-reference.md:1513:Emits a `console.warn` once per poison cycle if the world is poisoned (a prior tick failed 
and `recover()` has not been called). The warning identifies which API surface the caller routed through 
(`api='submit'`, `api='serialize'`, `api='transaction'`, etc.) so log readers can correlate the warning with the 
offending call site. Subsequent calls within the same poison cycle are silent; once `recover()` clears the poison, the 
next `warnIfPoisoned` call after a future failure will warn again.
